						               													<description>Players take the role of bunnies which start with 10 carrots each. Through card play, they try to make the other players lose carrots. Last player with any carrots left wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game play is similar to Uno, played over several short rounds. At the start of each round, every player gets a hand of 6 cards. In his turn, a player can discard a card that matches the number or color of the top card in the discard pile. If he is unable to do so, he has to draw a card. When one player has no cards left, the other players have to pay one carrot for each card left in their hands. Then a new round starts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Special rules: When a player is unable to play a card, he not only has to draw one, but also to stand up. When he plays a card in a later turn, he sits down again. There is a quite large number of special cards that allow to steal one carrot from each player that is currently standing. Other special cards make all other players stand up, or try to steal a carrot from a specific player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player without any carrots left is immediately out of the game. Winner is the last player with any carrots left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
